<subSubSection id="65A7652EC07E4B1CFF0149CEFD8C30CF" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C07E4B1CFF0149CEFD8C30CF" blockId="31.[192,1441,1179,1240]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFF0149CEFE8B30A2" bold="true" box="[192,316,1179,1205]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
In specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="EABD4D26C07E4B1CFE3649C9FD8230A1" authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2020" box="[503,565,1180,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rio">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFE3649C9FDBD30A1" box="[503,522,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFDD749C8FD8230A1" box="[534,565,1181,1206]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">rio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the elytral disc shows a distinct angular midelytral fascia, which is not the case in similar specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="EABD4D26C07E4B1CFE0849EBFD8230CF" authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2020" box="[457,565,1214,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiasta">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFE0849EBFE6B30CF" box="[457,476,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFE2949EBFD8230CF" box="[488,565,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">chiasta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65A7652EC07E4B1CFF0149B2FC3E324A" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C07E4B1CFF0149B2FD8C3224" blockId="31.[191,1441,1255,1587]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFF0149B2FEE53116" bold="true" box="[192,338,1255,1281]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFE9849BDFE333115" box="[345,388,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Size</emphasis>
. Length 14.0 mm; width 
<quantity id="EA459B40C07E4B1CFD6349BDFD4B3115" box="[674,764,1256,1282]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFCC649BDFCF63116" box="[775,833,1256,1281]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation id="B5862A20C07E4B1CFC5349BDFC593115" box="[914,1006,1256,1282]" captionStart="Figures 106–109" captionStartId="67.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1436,213,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-10@67.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="Figures 106–109. Habitus of Axina species. 106) Axina polycaula. 107) A. proxima. 108) A.rio. 109) A. villa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565031/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Fig. 108</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFC3949BDFB823115" box="[1016,1077,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Color</emphasis>
. Cranium bicolorous, frons castaneous, remainder black; antenna testaceous; thorax light castaneous; elytra bicolorous, mostly testaceous, humerus black, disc with 2 angular fasciae, one at middle and one broader before apex, midelytral fascia does not reach sutural margin, preapical fascia reaches sutural margin; legs bicolorous, distal ½ of femora and proximal 1/3 black, remainder of legs testaceous; abdomen testaceous. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFC83483AFCCB319E" box="[834,892,1391,1417]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium coarsely punctate, frons about as wide as length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 60/20. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFD0F48C4FCAB31BC" box="[718,796,1425,1451]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum coarsely punctate at sides, finely punctate in middle, with 2 tumescences, slightly concave at middle; PW/PL 140/170; elytra, asetiferous punctures scattered, punctures extend to elytral apical 3/4, width of interstitial spaces variable; EL/EW 600/100. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFB7F4880FA9131F8" box="[1214,1318,1493,1519]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="B5862A20C07E4B1CFF0848A2FEAB3205" box="[201,284,1527,1554]" captionStart="Figures 33–36" captionStartId="49.[192,279,645,671]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,614]" captionTargetId="figure-11@49.[192,1440,213,614]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="Figures 33–36. Aedeagi. 33) Axina polycaula. 34) A. ochra. 35) A. rio. 36) A. spina." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4564979" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4564979/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
), phallobasic lobes short, broad and slightly bent distally; phallic plates minutely serrate subapically; phallobasic apodeme abbreviated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C07E4B1CFF014B16FC3E324A" blockId="31.[192,905,1603,1630]" box="[192,905,1603,1630]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07E4B1CFF014B16FE81324A" bold="true" box="[192,310,1603,1629]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">Variation.</emphasis>
The two available specimens are quite homogeneous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65A7652EC07E4B1CFF014B38FC7D3290" box="[192,970,1645,1672]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
